id.description: Engine ID of the SNMP, official unique identifier. By default, the VRP uses an internal algorithm to automatically generate an engine ID. The engine ID consists of an enterprise number and device information. When the engine ID changes, all existing SNMP USM users will be deleted.

max-msg-size.description: Maximum length of packet supported by SNMP engine.

trap-source-interface-name.description: Name of the interface to send the trap message.

trap-source-ipv4-address.description: Source IP to send trap/notification message.

inform-timeout.description: Wait for the confirmation of the sent alarm till timeout.

inform-resend-times.description: Maximum number of times the trap packet should be sent if confirmation of alarm is not received.

inform-pend-number.description: Number of alarms sent for which confirmation is still pending.

packet-priority.description: The priority of SNMP response packet.

trap-packet-priority.description: The priority of SNMP trap packet.

usm-user-cmplx-check.description: Enable/disable USM user password complexity check switch.

local-user-cmplx-check.description: Enable/disable local user password complexity check switch.

protocol-source-interface-name.description: SNMP protocol source interface. The node /snmp:snmp/snmp:system/snmp:protocol-source-interface-name is not supported currently. You are advised to use the node /snmp:snmp/snmp:source-interfaces/snmp:source-interface/snmp:interface-name.

protocol-source-ipv6-address.description: SNMP protocol source IPv6 address. The node /snmp:snmp/snmp:system/snmp:protocol-source-ipv6-address is not supported currently. You are advised to use the node /snmp:snmp/snmp:ipv6-sources/snmp:ipv6-source/snmp:src-ipv6-address.

is-public-net.description: Enable/disable receive SNMP IPv4 message from public net.

is-ipv6-public-net.description: Enable/disable receive SNMP IPv6 message from public net.

ctx-engineid-check-enable.description: Enable/disable context engine id check switch.

ipv6-trap-source-ip.description: IPv6 source IP to send trap/notification message.

ipv6-trap-source-vpn.description: VPN instance name. The specified VPN instance must exist and IPv6-family must be enabled in the VPN instance.

isolate-ipv6-sources.description: List of configure isolate source IPv6 address.

target-hosts.description: List of target host for traps and informs.

nms-name.description: Unique name to identify target host entry.

target-inform-timeout.description: Timeout period of SNMP inform packets for the target.

target-inform-resend-times.description: Maximum number of time to re-transmit the SNMP inform packet if acknowledgement is not received from the target.

port-number.description: UDP port number used by network management to receive alarm messages.

params.description: This choice is augmented with case nodes containing configuration parameters specific to the security model.

security-level.description: Security level indicating whether to use authentication and encryption.

private-netmanager.description: Enable/disable private VB's for target host.

is-public-net.description: Enable/disable Public Net-manager for target Host.

ext-vb.description: Enable/disable extended VB's for target host.

notify-fltr-profile-name.description: To configure notification filter profile for target host.

retries-num.description: Number of retries made in sending inform.

pending-num.description: Number of informs which are waiting for acknowledgement.

dropped-num.description: Number of packets dropped while sending.

failed-num.description: Number of informs failed to receive acknowledgement.

interface-name.description: The specified source interface must exist and an IP address must be configured on the interface.

mib-views.description: List of VACM view to configure MIB subtree.

mib-view.description: Configure name of MIB View entry.

view-name.description: Name of subtree's MIB view entry.

group-name.description: Unique name to identify the SNMPv3 group.

security-level.description: Security level indicating whether to use authentication and encryption.

usm-users.description: List of USM users for SNMPv3.

user-name.description: Unique name to identify the USM user.

group-name.description: Name of the group where user belongs to.

left-lock-time.description: Left lock time of locked user.

local-users.description: List of local users for SNMPv3.

name.description: Unique name to identify the local user.

auth-protocol.description: Authentication protocol (md5 | sha | sha2-224 | sha2-256 | sha2-384 | sha2-512).

left-lock-time.description: Left lock time of locked user.

alias-name.description: Unique alias name to identify community.

notification.description: Configure the notification log global parameters.

notif-global-limit.description: Maximum number of notification entries to be stored.

name.description: Name to identify notify filter profile.

subtree.description: Subtree name of MIB object for trap/notification.

in-pkts.description: Number of packets received by the equipment.

out-pkts.description: Number of packets sent by the equipment.

in-bad-versions.description: Received received version is not Supported by SNMP engine for these number of packets.

in-bad-cmmty-names.description: Number of packets the device received with invalid group name.

in-bad-cmmty-users.description: Number of packets received by the device with group name corresponding to permission error.

in-asn-parse-errs.description: Number of packets received with ASN.1/BER errors.

in-too-bigs.description: Number of packets received by the SNMP protocol entities having error status field value 'in-too-bigs'.

in-nosuch-names.description: Number of packets received by the SNMP protocol entities having error status field value 'in-nosuch-names'.

in-bad-values.description: Number of packets received by the SNMP protocol entities having error status field value 'in-bad-values'.

in-read-onlys.description: Number of packets received by the SNMP protocol entities having error status field value 'in-read-onlys'.

in-gen-errs.description: Number of packets received by the SNMP protocol entities having error status field value 'in-gen-errs'.

in-total-req-vars.description: This number indicates the success of the SNMP entities to obtain the value from the nodes of MIB.

in-total-set-vars.description: This number indicates the success of the SNMP entities to set the value of the nodes of MIB.

in-get-reqs.description: Number of packets of 'Get' type received and processed by the equipment.

in-get-nexts.description: Number of packets of 'Get-Next' type received and processed by the equipment.

in-set-reqs.description: Number of packets of 'Set' type received and processed by the equipment.

in-get-resps.description: Number of packets of 'Get-Response' type received and processed by the equipment.

in-traps.description: Number of packets of 'Trap' type received and processed by the equipment.

out-too-bigs.description: Number of PDU generated by the SNMP protocol entities having error status field value 'outTooBig'.

out-nosuch-names.description: Number of PDU generated by the SNMP protocol entities having error status field value 'NoSuchName'.

out-bad-values.description: Number of PDU generated by the SNMP protocol entities having error status field value 'BadValue'.

out-get-reqs.description: Number of packets of 'Get' type generated by the equipment.

out-get-nexts.description: Number of packets of 'Get-Next' type generated by the equipment.

out-set-reqs.description: Number of packets of 'set' type generated by the equipment.

out-get-resps.description: Number of packets of 'Get Response' type generated by the equipment.

out-traps.description: Number of packets of 'Trap' type generated by the equipment.

in-get-bulks.description: Number of packets of 'Get-Bulk' type received and processed by the equipment.

out-get-bulks.description: Number of packets of 'Get-Bulk' type generated by the equipment.

in-informs.description: Number of packets of 'Inform' type received and processed by the equipment.

in-proxy-pkts.description: Number of proxy packets received by the equipment.

unknown-user-mame.description: Number of packets with unknown userName received and discarded by the equipment.

wrong-digests.description: Number of packets not having the expected digest value, received and dropped by the equipment.

unsuppt-sec-levs.description: Number of packets with invalid/unknown security level received and discarded by the equipment.

unknown-engine-ids.description: Number of packets received from an unknown engine ID which are dropped by equipment.

decryption-errs.description: Number of packets dropped by the equipment due to the failure of decrypting the packet.

unknown-sec-model.description: Number of packets discarded because references do not support security model.

inval-msgs.description: Total number of packets discarded because they contained illegal information.

unknown-pduhandle.description: Total number of packets with unknown PDU handle discarded by the equipment.

total-log-entrs.description: Current number of notification log entries.
